Title: Cannabidiol Expanded Access Study in Medically Refractory Sturge-Weber Syndrome
Outcome Measures: Change in seizure frequency|Change in average seizure duration by seizure type|Change in the number of episodes of status epilepticus, defined as convulsive seizure lasting longer than 10 minutes|Change in the number of uses of rescue medication|Change in the number of ER visits/ hospitalizations
Sponsor/Collaborators: Anne Comi, MD|GW Pharmaceuticals Ltd.|Faneca 66 Foundation|Hugo W. Moser Research Institute at Kennedy Krieger, Inc.
Study Designs: Intervention Model: Single Group Assignment|Masking: None (Open Label)|Primary Purpose: Treatment
Locations: Kennedy Krieger Institute, Baltimore, Maryland, United States

Title: Aspirin Attenuates Inflammation in Human Cerebral Aneurysms
